# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Yonca AI — Chainlit Ignore Configuration
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# PURPOSE: Disable Chainlit's default local file storage (.files/)
#
# This is a PRODUCTION BEST PRACTICE based on the Twelve-Factor App methodology.
# Yonca AI uses PostgreSQL for file storage instead (see storage_postgres.py).
#
# WHY PostgreSQL INSTEAD OF LOCAL .files/?
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   1. STATELESSNESS
#      In cloud deployments (Docker, Kubernetes, Render), containers are ephemeral.
#      If a container crashes or you deploy a new version, the .files/ folder is lost.
#      PostgreSQL ensures files survive container restarts and deployments.
#
#   2. LOAD BALANCING
#      If you have 2+ app instances behind a load balancer:
#        - User A uploads a file → saved to Instance 1's .files/
#        - User B requests the file → hits Instance 2 → "404 Not Found"
#      PostgreSQL ensures ANY instance can serve ANY file.
#
#   3. SINGLE BACKUP TRUTH
#      Running `pg_dump` backs up Users + Conversations + Files in one command.
#      No need to synchronize database backups with filesystem backups.
#
#   4. ACID COMPLIANCE
#      File uploads are transactional. You won't end up with:
#        - A database record pointing to a missing file
#        - A "ghost file" on disk with no database record
#
# ARCHITECTURE DECISION
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# We are NOT bypassing Chainlit's features. We are using its PLUGGABLE ARCHITECTURE.
# Chainlit provides BaseStorageClient abstract class.
# We implement PostgresStorageClient which inherits from BaseStorageClient.
# This is the industry-standard way to customize storage for production.
#
# REFERENCES:
#   - storage_postgres.py          ← Implementation
#   - docs/zekalab/11-CHAINLIT-STRUCTURE.md  ← Full documentation
#   - https://12factor.net/processes        ← Twelve-Factor App: Statelessness
#
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Ignore local file storage — all files go to PostgreSQL
.files/
